    "long_instructions": "## HTTP Cats for HTTP Requests Exploration\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n1. Click on the link to visit HTTP Cats.\r\n2. **Observe the different HTTP status codes** displayed on the site\r\n   - Each cat image represents a different HTTP response code (e.g., 200 OK, 404 Not Found)\r\n3. **Open the Developer Tools (Network Tab)** in your browser:\r\n   - **On Chrome:** Press `Ctrl + Shift + I` (Windows) or `Cmd + Option + I` (Mac), then go to the **Network** tab.\r\n   - **On Firefox:** Press `Ctrl + Shift + E (Windows)` or `Cmd + Option + E` (Mac).\r\n4. **Click on different HTTP status codes** on the site and observe how your browser sends requests and receives responses.\r\n5. **Look at the Network tab and find the request details:**\r\n   - **Status Code** - What response did the server send?\r\n   - **Headers** - What information was included in the request and response?\r\n   - **Timing** - How long did it take to load?\r\n6. **Explore different status codes** to see how servers communicate different types of responses.",
